Intracranial metastasis of thymoma: report of three cases. Thymoma with metastasis to the central nervous system is extremely rare. Herein, three rare cases of thymoma with intracranial metastasis are reported. Case 1 (thymoma, B3 in the WHO classification) cranial magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) revealed a mass lesion with a ring enhancement effect in the right temporal lobe. The cystic and hemorrhagic lesion was subtotally removed and radiation therapy of 40 Gy was administered to the tumor cavity containing the remains of the tumor around the ependyma. The patient received combination chemotherapy with carboplatin and gemcitabine hydrochloride, and he was discharged 3 months after the operation. Case 2 [(thymoma, C (thymic carcinoma)]